definitions.text:
I desire earnestly, long for; I have a strong affection for, love
                  fervently.
the eighth, one of eight, with seven others.
(properly: bulk, mass, hence) a weight, burden, encumbrance.
this here, this, that, he, she, it.
I lead, guide; met: I instruct, teach.
a leader, guide; met: an instructor, teacher.
I travel, pursue a way, journey.

I torment, pain; mid. and pass: I am tormented, pained; I suffer acute
                  pain, physical or mental.
pain, sorrow, distress, of body or mind.

Uzziah, son of Joram and father of Jotham, and king of Judah from about
                  785 to 746 B.C., an ancestor of Jesus.
a linen cloth, a sheet, sail.
a house, household, dwelling; meton: goods, property, means.
one of a family, whether child or servant.

I erect a building, build; fig. of the building up of character: I
                  build up, edify, encourage.
the act of building, a building, edification

(a) the act of building, (b) a building, (c) met: spiritual
                  advancement, edification.
I am a steward, manage a household.
management of household affairs, stewardship, administration.
a household manager, a steward, guardian.

(a) a house, the material building, (b) a household, family, lineage,
                  nation.

(properly: the land that is being inhabited, the land in a state of
                  habitation), the inhabited world, that is, the Roman world, for all outside it was
                  regarded as of no account.
slothful, backward, hesitating; of things: irksome.
of or belonging to the eighth day, eight days old.

(a) especially in plur: few, (b) in sing: small; hence, of time: short,
                  of degree: light, slight, little.
I despise, hold in low esteem, make light of.
complete in every part, sound, perfect
complete in every part, sound, perfect, entire.
I howl, lament loudly, cry aloud, bewail.
Olympas, a Christian man in Rome.

an unripe fig, one which, not ripening in due time, grows through the
                  winter and falls off in the spring.
wholly, altogether, actually, really; with negative: not at all.

I consort with, associate with, commune with; particularly, I talk
                  (converse) with.
I swear, take an oath, promise with an oath.
with one mind, unanimously, with one accord, at the same time.

of like feelings, having similar passions and feelings, of like
                  infirmities.
like, similar to, resembling, of equal rank.
I make like, liken; I compare.

(originally: a thing made like something else), a likeness, or rather:
                  form; a similitude.
in like manner, similarly, in the same way, equally.

(a) I promise, agree, (b) I confess, (c) I publicly declare, (d) a
                  Hebraism, I praise, celebrate.
of the same trade or craft
of the same trade or craft.
together, at the same place and time.

(originally adj: useful, hence the play upon words in Philemon 10, 11,
                  and very common as slave name), Onesimus, a slave of Philemon, a Christian of
                  Colossae.
Onesiphorus, a Christian of the province of Asia.
I help, profit, have joy of
I profit, benefit, help; mid: I have profit, derive benefit.
I give a name to, mention
I give a name to, mention, call upon the name of.

vinegar, sour wine mixed with water, a common drink of Roman
                  soldiers.
a crevice (in a rock), a cave, an opening, hole.
of what kind or manner, of what sort.
I appear, am seen (by), let myself be seen (by).
how, in order that, so that
how, in order that, so that, that.
a spectacle, vision, that which is seen.
I see, look upon, experience, perceive, discern, beware.
a fathom, about five or six feet
a fathom, about five or six feet.

I stretch forth, mid: I hanker after, long for, am eager for, aspire
                  to.
I walk in a straight course, walk uprightly
I walk in a straight course, walk uprightly.
I cut straight; met: I handle correctly, teach rightly.
I rise early, come in the morning
I rise early, come in the morning.

I separate, mark off by boundaries; I determine, appoint,
                  designate.
the boundaries of a place, hence: districts, territory.
I adjure by, charge solemnly by
I adjure by, charge solemnly by.
the taking of an oath, an oath
the taking of an oath, an oath.
a setting of boundaries, definite limit
a setting of boundaries, definite limit; plur: bounds.
as often as, as many times as.
holy, pious, godly, beloved of God.
how much, how great, how many
how much, how great, how many, as great as, as much.
that, since, because; may introduce direct discourse.
where, whither, when, in what place.
woe!, alas!, uttered in grief or denunciation.
by no means, not at all.
neither, nor, not even, and not.
in heaven, belonging to heaven, heavenly, from heaven.

heaven, (a) the visible heavens: the atmosphere, the sky, the starry
                  heavens, (b) the spiritual heavens.
Urbanus, a Christian in Rome, fellow-worker of Paul.
Uriah, husband of Bathsheba the mother of Solomon.
(a) the ear, (b) met: the faculty of perception.
by no means, not at all
by no means, not at all.

(a) a debtor, one who owes, one who is indebted, (b) one who has sinned
                  against another (an Aramaism), a sinner.
a debt, a duty, what is due.
O that! I wish! Would that!
O that! I wish! Would that!, followed by indicative.
service rendered only while the master watches
eye-service; service rendered only while the master watches.
the eye; fig: the mind's eye.
a serpent, snake; used of the devil or Satan.
the brow, a ridge (of a mountain).
I gather a crowd, make a riot.
a crowd, mob, the common people.
(a) the face, countenance, (b) the features, outward appearance.
